trans-unit.source: For non-empty collections, Count() enumerates the entire sequence, while Any() stops at the first item or the first item that satisfies a condition.
trans-unit.target: For non-empty collections, Count() enumerates the entire sequence, while Any() stops at the first item or the first item that satisfies a condition.

trans-unit.source: Count() is used where Any() could be used instead to improve performance.
trans-unit.target: Count() is used where Any() could be used instead to improve performance.

trans-unit.source: Do not use Count() when Any() can be used
